headline.main: JAPANESE RAIDED NORTH AND SOUTH; Ammunition Ship Believed Sunk in Solomons as Other Points in Area Are Bombed ONLY ONE U.S. PLANE LOST Enemy Positions on Kiska Are Pounded for Two Days in Row -- Camp Region Hit

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, March 1 -- Army and Navy fliers, operating over a wide area of the South Pacific, made a series of raids on Japanese strongholds over the week-end and, among other results, blew up a cargo ship believed to have been loaded with ammunition, a Navy communique announced today.
abstract: Alaska: US planes raid Kiska; hit camp area
